{
  "stem": "17720.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 83.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The Bulgarian king that was suppose to put his signature for the final deportation, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] was called by Hitler, was asked by Hitler to go to arrive to-- for a certain meeting in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He never came back.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Well, he came back as a form of a cadaver.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "His body already was transported in the plane.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They-- some people say that he was poisoned.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Somebody-- other people said that he was killed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It was not known exactly what happened.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It only was known that Hitler was asking him to do two things.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "One was to transport the Jews, and the other to put the Bulgarian soldiers on the Eastern Front against the Russians.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And obviously the answer of the king, Boris III, in both of these questions were negative.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Because he knew that in both of these [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] events, he will touch very deeply the soul of Bulgarian people, and will have tremendously big problems.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "First of all, Bulgarian people, Bulgarian soldiers, were not going to shoot Russian soldiers.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Perhaps they would kill or turn their rifles to their own officers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And the second thing was that Bulgarian population, in-- in-- in large, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] had basically a feeling of very great sympathies towards the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the people of the villages where they were transported had some kind of a very much this kind of Slavic attitudes of mercy toward these people.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "That they see that they are basically honest people that are trying within their very meager miserable means to live one honest life, never to steal, never to kill.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
